1
00:00:11,367 --> 00:00:15,200
I really don't know
where your children are.

2
00:00:15,267 --> 00:00:17,133
I was so dumb that
I went against you.

3
00:00:17,200 --> 00:00:19,533
I will not interfere
with whatever you want to do.

4
00:00:19,600 --> 00:00:20,833
You care about nothing
but Mookie!

5
00:00:20,900 --> 00:00:22,200
- Mookie!
- Hey, hey!

6
00:00:22,267 --> 00:00:22,967
- Oh, no!
- Mother!

7
00:00:23,033 --> 00:00:24,500
You're heartless!

8
00:00:24,567 --> 00:00:26,100
If I'm heartless,

9
00:00:26,167 --> 00:00:29,867
I won't get affected that
I couldn't find your siblings!

10
00:00:29,933 --> 00:00:32,500
Do you know where they are now?

11
00:00:32,567 --> 00:00:34,167
I tried to find them.

12
00:00:34,267 --> 00:00:36,533
But I still don't know
where they are.

13
00:00:36,600 --> 00:00:38,100
Please forgive me, Emma.

14
00:00:38,167 --> 00:00:39,600
You don't know how
to be a mother.

15
00:00:39,667 --> 00:00:41,000
You won't understand.

16
00:00:41,067 --> 00:00:42,467
The storage room
is already dirty.

17
00:00:42,533 --> 00:00:44,000
Can you please clean it?

18
00:00:44,067 --> 00:00:45,567
Where's my necklace?

19
00:00:45,633 --> 00:00:46,700
Hello, Astrid?

20
00:00:46,767 --> 00:00:48,467
Are you ready
to make it up to me?

21
00:00:48,533 --> 00:00:50,167
I knew it.

22
00:00:50,233 --> 00:00:51,533
Sir, arrest that woman.

23
00:00:51,600 --> 00:00:53,367
She's the woman who broke
into our house the other night.

24
00:00:53,433 --> 00:00:56,433
And now, she's caught red-handed
stealing from us again!

25
00:01:31,000 --> 00:01:31,700
Wait.

26
00:01:31,767 --> 00:01:33,300
I didn't steal this.

27
00:01:33,367 --> 00:01:35,467
Stop denying it!

28
00:01:35,533 --> 00:01:38,767
You're caught in the act, Emma!

29
00:01:38,833 --> 00:01:41,867
Sir, she told me
to clean this place.

30
00:01:41,967 --> 00:01:44,900
And then, I saw this.
I was about to return it to you.

31
00:01:44,967 --> 00:01:48,967
I told you to clean,
not to steal.

32
00:01:49,033 --> 00:01:51,233
I didn't know you were itching
to take away our things.

33
00:01:51,300 --> 00:01:52,867
You know that's not true.

34
00:01:52,933 --> 00:01:56,567
I give Flor even the smallest
coin I find in the laundry.

35
00:01:56,633 --> 00:02:00,267
You probably planned all that
to earn our trust.

36
00:02:01,100 --> 00:02:02,900
Do you think you hit
the jackpot?

37
00:02:02,967 --> 00:02:05,067
You can't fool me, Emma.

38
00:02:05,133 --> 00:02:06,933
Ma'am, I can't fool you.

39
00:02:07,000 --> 00:02:07,567
Sir!
Sir, please believe me.

40
00:02:08,533 --> 00:02:10,367
I can't fool anyone.

41
00:02:12,000 --> 00:02:15,500
Flor, is something
going on inside?

42
00:02:15,600 --> 00:02:17,300
Wait, let's listen.

43
00:02:23,500 --> 00:02:25,400
Is that Mommy Emma?

44
00:02:27,333 --> 00:02:28,733
Yes, that's Mommy Emma.

45
00:02:31,200 --> 00:02:34,733
Flor, why didn't you tell me
Mommy Emma is here?

46
00:02:36,100 --> 00:02:38,000
Your mom doesn't
want you to know.

47
00:02:38,067 --> 00:02:39,233
You know her.

48
00:02:39,800 --> 00:02:41,933
Can you please help me?

49
00:02:42,000 --> 00:02:43,500
Do me a favor, please.

50
00:02:43,567 --> 00:02:45,267
Please bring me to Mommy Emma.

51
00:02:45,900 --> 00:02:47,000
Here you go again, Mookie.

52
00:02:47,100 --> 00:02:49,600
You know I can't do that.

53
00:02:49,667 --> 00:02:52,000
Your mom told me
that you should stay here,

54
00:02:52,067 --> 00:02:54,367
and I can't bring you
wherever Emma is.

55
00:02:55,167 --> 00:02:56,967
I'll be in trouble if I do that.

56
00:02:57,033 --> 00:03:00,400
I only want to know
what's happening inside.

57
00:03:00,467 --> 00:03:03,667
Mom might do something to her.

58
00:03:04,833 --> 00:03:05,867
I work decently.

59
00:03:05,933 --> 00:03:09,000
And I won't ruin my name
for this necklace.

60
00:03:09,067 --> 00:03:12,100
I bought this necklace
as a gift for my daughter.

61
00:03:12,167 --> 00:03:13,833
And now, you've tried
to steal it?

62
00:03:13,900 --> 00:03:14,733
What for?

63
00:03:14,800 --> 00:03:16,500
To feed your family?

64
00:03:16,567 --> 00:03:17,833
Yes, we're poor.

65
00:03:17,900 --> 00:03:20,567
But I can't eat anything
that came from stealing.

66
00:03:20,667 --> 00:03:21,567
Sir!

67
00:03:21,633 --> 00:03:23,500
Sir, you can ask
the other maid, Flor.

68
00:03:23,567 --> 00:03:26,133
And her daughter, Mookie!

69
00:03:26,200 --> 00:03:27,267
They will tell you the truth.

70
00:03:27,333 --> 00:03:30,200
Don't you dare drag my daughter
into this!

71
00:03:30,267 --> 00:03:32,267
Sir, you can ask
my former employers.

72
00:03:32,333 --> 00:03:35,067
I didn't commit any crime
against them.

73
00:03:35,133 --> 00:03:36,100
You can ask them, Sir.

74
00:03:36,167 --> 00:03:37,667
I'm begging you.

75
00:03:37,733 --> 00:03:39,733
Flor, please.

76
00:03:39,800 --> 00:03:40,833
Bring me to...

77
00:03:40,900 --> 00:03:41,400
What are you trying to do?
Come on.

78
00:03:42,233 --> 00:03:43,333
What are you doing?

79
00:03:43,400 --> 00:03:45,367
Do you want me to get fired?

80
00:03:45,433 --> 00:03:46,867
You're so stubborn.

81
00:03:46,933 --> 00:03:49,267
Mom won't do that.

82
00:03:49,333 --> 00:03:51,933
She needs you here.

83
00:03:53,533 --> 00:03:55,833
Just do what your mom says.

84
00:03:55,933 --> 00:03:56,533
Flor?

85
00:03:56,600 --> 00:03:57,800
Madame is here.

86
00:03:57,867 --> 00:03:58,733
- Flor!
- She's calling me.

87
00:03:58,800 --> 00:04:00,100
Stay here. Be quiet.

88
00:04:00,167 --> 00:04:01,467
Don't go anywhere.

89
00:04:01,533 --> 00:04:02,567
Ma'am?

90
00:04:12,333 --> 00:04:14,700
Aren't you going to arrest her?

91
00:04:14,767 --> 00:04:17,567
Should I call
Colonel Albert Magno?

92
00:04:17,633 --> 00:04:19,867
Ma'am, just explain everything
at the police station.

93
00:04:19,933 --> 00:04:21,700
You can give us
your statement there.

94
00:04:23,200 --> 00:04:24,100
Go get her.
Sir.

95
00:04:24,933 --> 00:04:26,100
Sir, I didn't do anything wrong.

96
00:04:26,167 --> 00:04:27,133
Sir.

97
00:04:27,200 --> 00:04:29,500
Ma'am, I'm not doing
anything wrong to you!

98
00:04:29,600 --> 00:04:30,700
Why are you doing this to me?

99
00:04:30,767 --> 00:04:32,967
Is it because I became close
to your daughter?

100
00:04:33,033 --> 00:04:35,267
You did this to yourself, Emma.

101
00:04:36,200 --> 00:04:37,900
Arrest her.

102
00:04:37,967 --> 00:04:39,133
Go.

103
00:04:39,200 --> 00:04:39,967
Ma'am!

104
00:04:40,667 --> 00:04:41,967
Sir, I'm not stealing anything.

105
00:04:42,033 --> 00:04:43,333
Sir! Ma'am!

106
00:04:43,400 --> 00:04:43,767
Ma'am!

107
00:04:43,833 --> 00:04:45,067
Sir, please!

108
00:04:45,133 --> 00:04:45,933
Ma'am!

109
00:04:51,500 --> 00:04:52,533
Emma!

110
00:04:53,433 --> 00:04:54,600
- Emma!
- Mookie!

111
00:04:54,667 --> 00:04:55,500
Mookie!

112
00:05:10,600 --> 00:05:11,867
Mommy, what's happening?

113
00:05:11,933 --> 00:05:13,167
- Stay away from my daughter!
- Why are they arresting her?

114
00:05:13,233 --> 00:05:15,300
- Bring that woman with you!
- Why are they arresting Emma?

115
00:05:15,367 --> 00:05:16,800
- Mookie!
- Emma!

116
00:05:17,400 --> 00:05:18,933
Mommy, what's happening?

117
00:05:19,400 --> 00:05:20,200
Mookie!

118
00:05:20,267 --> 00:05:22,067
- Emma!
- Go, bring that woman.

119
00:05:22,133 --> 00:05:23,633
Emma!

120
00:05:27,900 --> 00:05:28,900
Emma!

121
00:05:28,967 --> 00:05:29,933
Arrest her.

122
00:05:32,967 --> 00:05:34,933
Emma!

123
00:05:40,233 --> 00:05:41,833
Emma!

124
00:05:59,333 --> 00:06:00,133
Yes?

125
00:06:01,267 --> 00:06:02,867
Are you waiting
for anything else?

126
00:06:09,533 --> 00:06:12,667
Mommy, why did
they bring Emma?

127
00:06:12,733 --> 00:06:14,767
What did she do wrong?

128
00:06:15,567 --> 00:06:18,667
That Emma stole your necklace.

129
00:06:19,667 --> 00:06:20,467
What?

130
00:06:21,167 --> 00:06:23,500
She's pretending to be your mom.

131
00:06:23,567 --> 00:06:28,467
But turns out, she was planning
to steal from us.

132
00:06:28,533 --> 00:06:31,300
Mommy, she can't do that.

133
00:06:31,367 --> 00:06:33,367
You're mistaken.

134
00:06:35,567 --> 00:06:38,033
So, are you calling me a liar?

135
00:06:42,033 --> 00:06:43,300
No, Mommy.

136
00:06:44,767 --> 00:06:46,833
You are not a liar.

137
00:06:49,033 --> 00:06:50,633
Let's talk later.

138
00:06:51,667 --> 00:06:52,867
I have to go to
the police station.

139
00:06:52,933 --> 00:06:56,600
I'll see to it that that woman
will rot in jail.

140
00:06:57,367 --> 00:06:58,167
Mommy, no.

141
00:06:58,933 --> 00:07:00,467
No, please, Mommy.

142
00:07:00,533 --> 00:07:03,867
Emma didn't do anything wrong.

143
00:07:03,933 --> 00:07:05,000
Why not?

144
00:07:07,833 --> 00:07:10,500
Don't you feel guilty
about what you do?

145
00:07:13,633 --> 00:07:16,567
You are ruining
another person's life.

146
00:07:17,500 --> 00:07:19,133
Really, Mookie?

147
00:07:21,233 --> 00:07:26,167
Are you taking that
laundress' side over me?

148
00:07:29,033 --> 00:07:30,533
I'm your mother.

149
00:07:40,433 --> 00:07:41,767
Sorry, Mommy.

150
00:07:42,600 --> 00:07:43,833
Sorry.

151
00:07:45,367 --> 00:07:46,633
You better be.

152
00:07:49,333 --> 00:07:50,900
Flor, bring her inside.

153
00:07:50,967 --> 00:07:52,133
Yes. Yes, Ma'am.

154
00:08:03,333 --> 00:08:04,767
Don't cry.

155
00:08:23,167 --> 00:08:25,267
Why are you here?
You're not allowed in here.

156
00:08:25,333 --> 00:08:26,767
I won't take long, Miss.

157
00:08:26,833 --> 00:08:29,100
Her mother has already left.

158
00:08:29,167 --> 00:08:31,033
She might come back right away.

159
00:08:31,100 --> 00:08:31,967
Go.

160
00:08:32,033 --> 00:08:35,033
- Leave.
- I only want to talk to Mookie.

161
00:08:35,100 --> 00:08:37,700
I might get in trouble.

162
00:08:46,633 --> 00:08:48,033
Dan, they want to put me
in jail.

163
00:08:48,100 --> 00:08:50,133
Can you please come and see me?

164
00:09:16,300 --> 00:09:17,000
Zayn...

165
00:09:17,067 --> 00:09:18,933
don't forget what I told you.

166
00:09:19,000 --> 00:09:19,700
You're only allowed to stay
for a couple of minutes.
You can't stay long.

167
00:09:20,600 --> 00:09:21,400
- Okay?
- Yes.

168
00:09:22,000 --> 00:09:23,033
I'll leave you for now.

169
00:09:23,100 --> 00:09:24,233
I'll be inside.

170
00:09:24,300 --> 00:09:25,067
Okay.

171
00:09:28,167 --> 00:09:30,267
Mookie, what's going on?

172
00:09:30,333 --> 00:09:32,033
Why did Emma get arrested?

173
00:09:40,733 --> 00:09:42,433
You left your things.

174
00:09:43,300 --> 00:09:44,067
Sir.

175
00:09:45,067 --> 00:09:47,167
Can you go over her stuff?

176
00:09:47,233 --> 00:09:49,833
She might have stolen
other things from me.

177
00:09:51,567 --> 00:09:52,867
Is this really yours?

178
00:09:52,933 --> 00:09:53,967
Yes, Sir.

179
00:09:56,667 --> 00:09:57,500
Let's check it.

180
00:10:11,200 --> 00:10:14,400
Do you know why Emma
was arrested?

181
00:10:18,600 --> 00:10:20,767
Mommy Emma isn't a thief.

182
00:10:22,833 --> 00:10:24,700
She won't steal anything.

183
00:10:27,467 --> 00:10:31,667
I dropped my necklace one time.

184
00:10:32,733 --> 00:10:34,900
She returned it to me
right away.

185
00:10:36,733 --> 00:10:39,333
That's why I'm sure
she's not a thief.

186
00:10:41,167 --> 00:10:45,033
If that's the case,
why don't you tell your mom?

187
00:10:46,467 --> 00:10:49,433
Because she doesn't
listen to me.

188
00:10:50,933 --> 00:10:52,800
These are just canned goods,
Ma'am.

189
00:10:53,533 --> 00:10:54,567
Grocery items.

190
00:10:54,633 --> 00:10:57,267
Canned goods from my house.

191
00:10:57,333 --> 00:10:59,067
Look at that.

192
00:11:00,067 --> 00:11:01,633
I already gave you a job,

193
00:11:01,700 --> 00:11:03,333
and you still managed
to steal from me.

194
00:11:03,400 --> 00:11:05,900
You turned my house
into a grocery store.

195
00:11:05,967 --> 00:11:07,367
Sir, she's lying.

196
00:11:07,433 --> 00:11:09,400
I didn't steal all that.

197
00:11:10,467 --> 00:11:11,767
You planted them!

198
00:11:11,833 --> 00:11:13,667
Even the necklace in the room!

199
00:11:16,667 --> 00:11:18,533
You know...

200
00:11:18,600 --> 00:11:21,133
I have a feeling that...

201
00:11:23,467 --> 00:11:25,700
mommy did that on purpose.

202
00:11:26,800 --> 00:11:28,167
Why would she do that?

203
00:11:28,733 --> 00:11:31,067
Because Mommy Emma
and I are close.

204
00:11:32,333 --> 00:11:35,300
Mommy wants to separate us.

205
00:11:35,367 --> 00:11:39,267
I'm not sure if what
I feel is right.

206
00:11:41,867 --> 00:11:42,633
But...

207
00:11:44,467 --> 00:11:46,133
Sometimes...

208
00:11:48,000 --> 00:11:53,533
Sometimes I wish Mommy Emma
was my mother.

209
00:11:55,700 --> 00:11:57,500
Does that make me
a bad daughter?

210
00:11:58,500 --> 00:11:59,567
Of course not.

211
00:12:00,667 --> 00:12:04,700
You're probably getting what you
need from your mom from Emma.

212
00:12:05,333 --> 00:12:08,467
The love and affection.

213
00:12:08,533 --> 00:12:10,133
You can't fake it.

214
00:12:12,533 --> 00:12:14,633
Get that woman away from me.

215
00:12:16,000 --> 00:12:18,267
I'm ready to give
my statement.

216
00:12:20,767 --> 00:12:21,600
Ma'am...

217
00:12:22,400 --> 00:12:23,733
Please relax.

218
00:12:24,933 --> 00:12:29,867
Are you really
going to sue her?

219
00:12:29,933 --> 00:12:34,567
This kind of case will
only waste your time.

220
00:12:35,333 --> 00:12:40,567
But if you agree to settle,

221
00:12:40,633 --> 00:12:45,967
she will pay ten times
the necklace's value.

222
00:12:46,033 --> 00:12:48,600
She can't pay
what she stole from me

223
00:12:48,700 --> 00:12:52,033
even if she sells her kidney.

224
00:12:52,800 --> 00:12:54,733
You know what, Zayn?

225
00:12:56,667 --> 00:12:57,600
When...

226
00:12:59,400 --> 00:13:01,567
Mommy Emma looked after me...

227
00:13:03,167 --> 00:13:08,067
I got better even
without medicine.

228
00:13:09,533 --> 00:13:11,167
Maybe that's why...

229
00:13:12,233 --> 00:13:14,133
mommy takes it against her.

230
00:13:15,633 --> 00:13:18,867
Even if Mommy Emma isn't
doing anything wrong.

231
00:13:20,567 --> 00:13:21,733
I've made up my mind.

232
00:13:22,900 --> 00:13:24,767
I won't settle.

233
00:13:26,000 --> 00:13:28,067
I want her to rot in jail.

234
00:13:28,733 --> 00:13:35,967
I will file a case, so that
no one will fall victim to her.

235
00:13:39,100 --> 00:13:40,467
Let's go. Come with me.

236
00:13:40,533 --> 00:13:41,367
Sir!

237
00:13:41,433 --> 00:13:42,667
Sir, wait.

238
00:13:42,733 --> 00:13:44,600
Sir, I'm telling the truth!

239
00:13:45,133 --> 00:13:45,733
Sir!

240
00:13:45,800 --> 00:13:47,400
Sir, I'm the victim here!

241
00:13:47,467 --> 00:13:49,433
Believe me, Sir!

242
00:13:49,500 --> 00:13:50,667
Sir!

243
00:14:04,200 --> 00:14:04,867
Sir!

244
00:14:06,000 --> 00:14:07,267
I didn't steal anything!

245
00:14:07,333 --> 00:14:08,867
I didn't steal the necklace!

246
00:14:08,933 --> 00:14:10,867
I didn't steal those groceries!

247
00:14:10,933 --> 00:14:12,200
I didn't take them!

248
00:14:12,267 --> 00:14:13,133
Ma'am!

249
00:14:13,200 --> 00:14:16,100
Ma'am Olive, tell them
the truth!

250
00:14:16,167 --> 00:14:17,567
You know the truth.

251
00:14:17,633 --> 00:14:19,633
I didn't steal anything!

252
00:14:20,467 --> 00:14:23,700
Make sure to file the case
within 24 hours.

253
00:14:23,767 --> 00:14:26,367
Spare no cost in expediting it.

254
00:14:26,433 --> 00:14:28,133
I've also talked to Judge Yumul.

255
00:14:28,233 --> 00:14:31,333
His secretary is waiting
for you at the fiscal's office.

256
00:14:31,400 --> 00:14:32,433
Do it now.

257
00:14:45,600 --> 00:14:48,633
Ma'am, I'll just talk
to my daughter.

258
00:14:48,700 --> 00:14:50,000
Emma Joseco.

259
00:14:50,067 --> 00:14:50,833
Go ahead.

260
00:14:50,900 --> 00:14:51,867
Thank you.

261
00:14:59,133 --> 00:14:59,833
Emma.

262
00:15:02,400 --> 00:15:03,167
Emma.

263
00:15:06,567 --> 00:15:07,200
Mother.

264
00:15:10,500 --> 00:15:11,133
Mother.

265
00:15:11,200 --> 00:15:13,033
How did you know?

266
00:15:13,100 --> 00:15:14,967
Your husband called me.

267
00:15:17,133 --> 00:15:18,867
Son of a gun, Emma.

268
00:15:18,933 --> 00:15:20,167
What is it this time?

269
00:15:21,100 --> 00:15:22,733
You just returned to your job.

270
00:15:24,667 --> 00:15:26,333
You saw it.

271
00:15:26,400 --> 00:15:28,767
I kneeled in front of that Olive

272
00:15:28,833 --> 00:15:30,767
so you could go back
to your job.

273
00:15:31,700 --> 00:15:32,267
I cried.

274
00:15:32,333 --> 00:15:33,733
Begged her.

275
00:15:33,800 --> 00:15:35,133
And here we go again?

276
00:15:35,233 --> 00:15:38,433
Mother, I hope you find out
first what really happened.

277
00:15:38,500 --> 00:15:40,700
I was accused of stealing.

278
00:15:41,433 --> 00:15:43,567
That woman is crazy.

279
00:15:44,367 --> 00:15:49,400
Is it because she's jealous that
her daughter is so fond of you?

280
00:15:49,467 --> 00:15:50,967
Is that why she's framing you up
for a crime?

281
00:15:51,800 --> 00:15:52,867
That's not right.

282
00:15:54,300 --> 00:15:55,100
Ma'am.

283
00:15:56,267 --> 00:15:58,133
Can you please help my daughter?

284
00:15:58,200 --> 00:15:59,900
She's not a thief, Ma'am.

285
00:15:59,967 --> 00:16:02,033
We're not taking any sides.

286
00:16:02,667 --> 00:16:05,667
We're just doing our jobs.

287
00:16:05,733 --> 00:16:07,033
- Ma'am, please...
- Emma.

288
00:16:07,567 --> 00:16:09,533
Mother.

289
00:16:09,633 --> 00:16:10,333
Emma.

290
00:16:12,833 --> 00:16:14,100
Take care of Emma.

291
00:16:14,900 --> 00:16:16,467
Mother, where are you going?

292
00:16:17,067 --> 00:16:21,867
If only I could give a statement
to the police, I would.

293
00:16:22,967 --> 00:16:25,333
I would tell them

294
00:16:25,400 --> 00:16:27,833
that Mommy Emma didn't
do anything wrong.

295
00:16:27,900 --> 00:16:29,067
That she was innocent.

296
00:16:31,133 --> 00:16:32,300
I have an idea.

297
00:16:33,200 --> 00:16:34,767
Maybe I can help you.

298
00:16:41,133 --> 00:16:43,700
Dan, I never wanted this
to happen.

299
00:16:43,800 --> 00:16:45,500
Emma, I'm here now.

300
00:16:45,567 --> 00:16:47,267
I will get you out of here.
Promise.

301
00:16:48,100 --> 00:16:50,900
I will find a way
to get you out.

302
00:16:51,900 --> 00:16:52,933
Sorry.

303
00:16:53,000 --> 00:16:55,500
Why are you saying sorry?

304
00:16:55,567 --> 00:16:57,300
You shouldn't say sorry.

305
00:16:57,367 --> 00:16:59,633
I know you're innocent.

306
00:17:00,467 --> 00:17:03,033
I'm dragging you
into my mess.

307
00:17:03,100 --> 00:17:05,633
Emma, this is our problem.

308
00:17:05,700 --> 00:17:06,900
We're a married couple.

309
00:17:07,667 --> 00:17:09,667
We will fight Olive.

310
00:17:10,733 --> 00:17:12,033
How?

311
00:17:12,100 --> 00:17:15,133
Ma'am Olive is wealthy.

312
00:17:15,233 --> 00:17:16,667
She has plenty of money
to pay the lawyer.

313
00:17:16,733 --> 00:17:18,067
She's influential.

314
00:17:18,133 --> 00:17:18,900
She has lots of connections.

315
00:17:18,967 --> 00:17:21,100
How can we win over her?

316
00:17:22,000 --> 00:17:25,267
Just trust me.
I will find a way.

317
00:17:26,500 --> 00:17:30,000
I just wish the fight was fair,
but it's not.

318
00:17:30,067 --> 00:17:32,167
The bad ones always win.

319
00:17:32,233 --> 00:17:34,333
Emma, don't give up. Come on.

320
00:17:37,300 --> 00:17:39,600
I'll find a way.
I'll get you out of here.

321
00:17:43,767 --> 00:17:45,400
I will fight for the truth.

322
00:17:46,233 --> 00:17:49,967
Emma, if there's anything
I'm holding onto, it's you.

323
00:18:13,100 --> 00:18:13,767
Stop!
Stop!

324
00:18:14,800 --> 00:18:15,633
Stop!

325
00:18:16,067 --> 00:18:17,033
Let's talk.

326
00:18:17,100 --> 00:18:18,367
Why did you frame up
my daughter?

327
00:18:20,100 --> 00:18:21,667
Stop! Get off!

328
00:18:21,767 --> 00:18:23,367
Show me what you got!

329
00:18:23,800 --> 00:18:25,300
Are you going to kill me?

330
00:18:25,367 --> 00:18:28,267
What is this woman doing?

331
00:18:28,333 --> 00:18:29,933
Ma'am, please just leave.

332
00:18:30,000 --> 00:18:31,233
No! I'm talking to her!

333
00:18:31,300 --> 00:18:32,900
She did me something wrong!

334
00:18:32,967 --> 00:18:33,900
It's okay.

335
00:18:33,967 --> 00:18:35,267
I can handle this.

336
00:18:36,200 --> 00:18:37,033
Madame.

337
00:18:38,700 --> 00:18:40,100
What do you need?

338
00:18:40,700 --> 00:18:42,367
Are you going to extort
money from me again?

339
00:18:43,367 --> 00:18:45,567
You know why I'm here.

340
00:18:46,133 --> 00:18:47,833
My daughter is innocent.

341
00:18:48,800 --> 00:18:50,767
So, I'm begging you.

342
00:18:52,433 --> 00:18:54,267
Please drop the case.

343
00:18:54,900 --> 00:18:57,433
And why would I do that?

344
00:18:57,533 --> 00:18:59,700
My daughter is not a thief.

345
00:18:59,767 --> 00:19:00,767
I'm telling you.

346
00:19:00,833 --> 00:19:02,333
She's not a thief.

347
00:19:03,700 --> 00:19:05,900
Why would I believe you?

348
00:19:06,767 --> 00:19:09,167
You, who's greedy for money?

349
00:19:09,233 --> 00:19:13,633
Clearly, Emma takes after you.

350
00:19:13,700 --> 00:19:15,133
No, Madame.

351
00:19:15,200 --> 00:19:16,500
Emma isn't that kind of person.

352
00:19:16,567 --> 00:19:17,867
I'm telling you.

353
00:19:17,933 --> 00:19:19,267
Please.

354
00:19:19,333 --> 00:19:20,867
Believe me.

355
00:19:23,267 --> 00:19:24,167
What are you doing?

356
00:19:25,033 --> 00:19:26,567
How dare you!

357
00:19:42,367 --> 00:19:44,033
Why do you stare at me
like that?

358
00:19:45,300 --> 00:19:46,767
What happened?

359
00:19:48,200 --> 00:19:55,967
A necklace brought out
Emma's true character.

360
00:19:57,567 --> 00:20:01,233
Mother, you shouldn't
have talked to Olive.

361
00:20:01,300 --> 00:20:03,133
You ended up hurt.

362
00:20:04,500 --> 00:20:06,733
I just can't sit
and do nothing.

363
00:20:07,333 --> 00:20:11,600
By the way, I'll meet
with Mon, my co-worker.

364
00:20:11,667 --> 00:20:14,067
He knows a lawyer.

365
00:20:14,133 --> 00:20:16,867
Maybe they can help us.

366
00:20:16,933 --> 00:20:18,367
Dream on.

367
00:20:19,033 --> 00:20:22,800
The court is biased and in favor
of the wealthy.

368
00:20:22,867 --> 00:20:24,733
Even if Emma tells the truth,

369
00:20:24,800 --> 00:20:28,867
they will still believe
Olive's lies.

370
00:20:28,933 --> 00:20:31,900
We should report it
to the radio.

371
00:20:31,967 --> 00:20:34,800
I don't want us
to be on the radio.

372
00:20:34,900 --> 00:20:36,167
Why should you be ashamed?

373
00:20:36,233 --> 00:20:38,100
You did nothing wrong.

374
00:20:38,167 --> 00:20:41,933
When your side of the story
airs, you'll be exonerated.

375
00:20:42,000 --> 00:20:43,967
Your name will be cleared.

376
00:20:44,833 --> 00:20:46,833
Mookie will get involved.

377
00:20:47,567 --> 00:20:51,800
We're going against Dra. Olive,
not the kid.

378
00:20:51,867 --> 00:20:55,500
Mom, I don't want to tarnish
the child's name and dignity.

379
00:20:55,567 --> 00:20:58,833
You worry about something
that hasn't happened yet, Emma.

380
00:20:58,900 --> 00:21:00,767
You're the one in prison.

381
00:21:00,833 --> 00:21:02,733
Don't you feel sorry
for yourself?

382
00:21:05,433 --> 00:21:07,800
Dan, can we not argue
about this?

383
00:21:10,700 --> 00:21:13,333
I'm getting pissed
with the situation.

384
00:21:14,200 --> 00:21:15,467
But not with you.

385
00:21:17,233 --> 00:21:19,833
I know you're just worried
about me.

386
00:21:20,767 --> 00:21:21,767
I have to go.

387
00:21:21,833 --> 00:21:24,700
I'll let you know
once I talk to the lawyer.

388
00:21:24,767 --> 00:21:26,000
I'll go ahead.

389
00:21:26,067 --> 00:21:26,767
Mother.

390
00:21:30,500 --> 00:21:32,167
How about you, Mother?

391
00:21:32,233 --> 00:21:34,467
You can go home, too.

392
00:21:34,533 --> 00:21:35,767
It might already be late.

393
00:21:36,733 --> 00:21:39,933
Go home and bring the food.

394
00:21:40,000 --> 00:21:41,233
I'll sleep here.

395
00:21:42,567 --> 00:21:44,067
I'll make myself a bed.

396
00:21:44,133 --> 00:21:45,300
Mother.

397
00:21:45,367 --> 00:21:46,300
You don't have to.

398
00:21:46,367 --> 00:21:49,167
It's more comfortable
to sleep at home.

399
00:21:50,400 --> 00:21:55,433
Do you think I can sleep at home
knowing you're here?

400
00:21:59,033 --> 00:22:00,900
I lost my twins already.

401
00:22:02,100 --> 00:22:05,667
I can't lose you, too.

402
00:22:06,500 --> 00:22:08,533
My siblings are twins?

403
00:22:09,233 --> 00:22:12,500
Emma is not opportunistic,
Mommy.

404
00:22:12,567 --> 00:22:14,100
Oh, please, Mookie.

405
00:22:14,167 --> 00:22:16,500
Stop defending that woman.

406
00:22:23,233 --> 00:22:24,167
I can't help it.

407
00:22:30,133 --> 00:22:32,367
I'm just wondering

408
00:22:32,433 --> 00:22:38,067
how my necklace ends up
in the dark room.

409
00:22:45,900 --> 00:22:47,800
Are you trying...

410
00:22:50,400 --> 00:22:52,833
to insinuate something?

411
00:22:52,900 --> 00:22:56,300
I know Emma isn't
that kind of person.

412
00:22:58,767 --> 00:22:59,733
Unless...

413
00:23:00,800 --> 00:23:02,167
she was framed up.

414
00:23:11,733 --> 00:23:13,533
I need to be brave.

415
00:23:14,167 --> 00:23:15,333
I need to be strong.

416
00:23:16,167 --> 00:23:18,300
I need to get myself up.

417
00:23:18,800 --> 00:23:23,400
I won't give up no matter how
hard and painful everything is.

418
00:23:23,500 --> 00:23:24,800
Flor, Mookie is missing!

419
00:23:24,867 --> 00:23:25,800
What?

420
00:23:25,867 --> 00:23:27,100
Call the guard! Hurry!

421
00:23:27,167 --> 00:23:27,767
Mommy Emma!

422
00:23:28,533 --> 00:23:29,300
Mommy Emma!

423
00:23:29,367 --> 00:23:30,333
Mookie!

424
00:23:30,400 --> 00:23:32,200
Don't you think
she went to Emma?

425
00:23:32,267 --> 00:23:34,067
Get my phone and my car keys.

426
00:23:34,133 --> 00:23:35,100
Hurry! It's in the room!

427
00:23:35,167 --> 00:23:35,967
- Hurry up!
- Yes, yes.

428
00:23:36,033 --> 00:23:39,100
You can now walk on your own,
Dear.

429
00:23:39,167 --> 00:23:41,500
You're my inspiration,
Mommy Emma.

430
00:23:41,567 --> 00:23:44,400
The miracle worker in my life.

431
00:23:44,467 --> 00:23:45,567
You're a beast, Emma.

432
00:23:47,467 --> 00:23:50,500
You can't take my daughter
away from me.
